2026-05-23 | Check if Array is Sorted and Rotated

	Question
Return true if array is sorted and rotated.
	Key Insight
In a sorted rotated array:
		there can be at most ONE position
		where order decreases.
Example:
		[3,4,5,1,2]
				only one drop: 5 → 1
Invalid:
		[3,4,2,5,1]
				two drops
Need circular check:
		last → first also matters.
	Approach
1.	Count number of decreases:
		nums[i] > nums[(i+1)%n]
2.	If count > 1:
		return false
3.	Otherwise:
		return true
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool check(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int count = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            if(nums[i] > nums[(i + 1) % n]){
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count <= 1;
    }
};
	Key Insight
A sorted rotated array has:
		only one breaking point
		where larger element comes before smaller one.  
More than one such break means:
		array cannot come from sorted rotation.
